The purpose of the macro is to format a sheet by:
Freezing panes at row 8.
Look through column A, find the first cell(Cb) containing the text "(Balance forward" and the first cell(Ct) containing the text "Totals for" and grouping from rows Cb + 1 and Ct - 1
Loop through column A to group all instances.
Collapse all groups. 
Comma style formats for Columns I,J,K, and O.
Find last row(LR) with text in column A. From Cell M1 to MLR cell color is -0.0999786370433668

Find the row(LR1) first cell in column A containing the text "Totals for 1". Set cell NLR1="Accounts Receivable:" Do not loop. Stop once cell is found.
Find the row(LR2) first cell in column A containing the text "Totals for 2". Set cell NLR2="Accounts Payable:" Do not loop. Stop once cell is found.
Find the row(LR2) first cell in column A containing the text "Totals for 5". Set cell NLR3="Expenses:" Do not loop. Stop once cell is found.
